[% META
    title = 'AI Controller - Ollama Integration & Multi-Turn Conversations'
    description = 'Comprehensive documentation for AI controller covering all 16+ methods, guest session support, JSON API endpoints, multi-turn conversations, model management, server configuration, and conversation persistence'
    roles = 'admin,developer,editor,user'
    TemplateType = 'controller'
    category = 'controllers,ai,ollama'
    page_version = '1.11'
    last_updated = '2026-01-08'
    site_specific = ''
%]

[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/AI.tt,v 1.11 2026/01/08 zencoder-docsync Exp ' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h1 id="ai-controller">AI Controller - Ollama Integration & Multi-Turn Conversations</h1>
            
            <div id="toc" class="alert alert-info">
                <strong>Contents:</strong>
                <ul style="margin: 10px 0 0 20px;">
                    <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#authentication">Authentication & Guest Sessions</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#main-interface">Main Interface & Configuration</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#api-endpoints">JSON API Endpoints</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#form-endpoints">Web Form Endpoints</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#conversations">Conversation Management</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#model-management">Model Management</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#server-management">Server Management</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#implementation-details">Implementation Details</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#methods-reference">Complete Methods Reference</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="alert alert-success" id="recent-changes">
                <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">📝 Recent Changes (v1.11 - Jan 8, 2026)</h3>
                <ul style="margin: 5px 0 0 20px;">
                    <li><strong>AI.pm Code Updates:</strong> 3 commits with controller enhancements and bug fixes</li>
                    <li><strong>Documentation Sync:</strong> Updated version to 1.11 to reflect latest code state</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit Trail:</strong> Documentation now synced via automated audit workflow</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin: 10px 0 0 0; font-size: 0.9em; color: #666;">For complete change history, see git commit history of <code>lib/Comserv/Controller/AI.pm</code></p>
            </div>
            
            <section id="overview">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    The <code>AI</code> controller (Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/AI.pm) provides comprehensive 
                    AI/Ollama integration for the Comserv application. It supports:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Interactive AI chat interface with guest user support</li>
                    <li>JSON API endpoints for programmatic access</li>
                    <li>Multi-turn conversation persistence with conversation history</li>
                    <li>Ollama model management (pull, test, remove)</li>
                    <li>Multi-server Ollama configuration (localhost + network)</li>
                    <li>Automatic server startup on query failure</li>
                    <li>Guest session management with UUID tracking</li>
                    <li>Comprehensive logging with debug support</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <strong>Ollama Model Support:</strong> Utilizes <code>Comserv::Model::Ollama</code> for LLM interaction.
                    Supports various models including llama3.1, mistral, neural-chat, and custom models.
                </p>
            </section>
            
            <section id="authentication">
                <h2>Authentication & Guest Sessions</h2>
                
                <h3>Authentication Model</h3>
                <p>
                    The AI controller implements a <strong>guest-first</strong> authentication model:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Authenticated Users:</strong> Full access with user_id from session</li>
                    <li><strong>Guest Users:</strong> Full access with auto-assigned guest session ID (UUID)</li>
                    <li><strong>No Authentication Blocks:</strong> All endpoints accessible to both authenticated and guest users</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Guest Session Management</h3>
                <p>
                    Guest users are automatically created and tracked:
                </p>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Field</th>
                        <th>Value</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>user_id</code></td>
                        <td>199</td>
                        <td>Fixed guest user ID in database (must exist)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>guest_session_id</code></td>
                        <td>UUID string</td>
                        <td>Unique session identifier (created once per browser session)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>username</code></td>
                        <td>Guest-XXXXXXXX</td>
                        <td>Display name (first 8 chars of UUID)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <strong>⚠ Important:</strong> Guest user with ID 199 must exist in users table for conversation persistence to work.
                    Verify with: <code>SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users WHERE id = 199;</code>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="main-interface">
                <h2>Main Interface & Configuration</h2>
                
                <h3>Index Action</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>GET /ai</code></p>
                <p>
                    Main AI interface page displaying:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Interactive query form for single-shot AI queries</li>
                    <li>Current Ollama configuration (host, port, model)</li>
                    <li>Available models (installed + catalog)</li>
                    <li>Model/server selection controls (admin-only)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Configuration Helper</h3>
                <p>
                    <code>_get_current_ollama_config($c, $can_select_model)</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Initializes Ollama configuration with:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Current host and port from session or config</li>
                    <li>Default model selection</li>
                    <li>List of installed models from server</li>
                    <li>Permission-based UI adjustments (admin vs user views)</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            
            <section id="api-endpoints">
                <h2>JSON API Endpoints</h2>
                
                <p>
                    API endpoints accept and return JSON, supporting programmatic AI integration.
                    All endpoints support both authenticated users and guests.
                </p>
                
                <h3>Generate Endpoint</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>POST /ai/generate</code></p>
                <p><strong>Content-Type:</strong> application/json (or form data)</p>
                
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Parameter</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>Required</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>prompt</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>✅ Yes</td>
                        <td>User's question or prompt to AI</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>format</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>'json' for JSON response format, text otherwise</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>system</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>System prompt to override default AI behavior</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>page_context</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Context of page where request originated (e.g., 'docs', 'help')</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>conversation_id</code></td>
                        <td>integer</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Existing conversation to continue (omit for new conversation)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>agent_id</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>ID of AI agent/assistant handling request</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <h3>Response Format</h3>
                <pre><code>
{
  "success": true,
  "response": "AI's answer to prompt",
  "conversation_id": 42,
  "message_id": 123,
  "model_used": "llama3.1",
  "processing_time_ms": 2500,
  "is_new_conversation": false
}
                </code></pre>
                
                <h3>Automatic Server Startup</h3>
                <p>
                    If Ollama server is not running on localhost:11434:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>System detects connection failure</li>
                    <li>Calls <code>start_server()</code> to start Ollama</li>
                    <li>Automatically retries query after startup</li>
                    <li>Returns response or error if startup fails</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>Chat Endpoint</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>POST /ai/chat</code></p>
                <p>
                    Multi-turn conversation endpoint supporting conversation history and persistence.
                </p>
                
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Parameter</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>Required</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>prompt</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>✅ Yes</td>
                        <td>User's message</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>model</code></td>
                        <td>string</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Model to use (default: configured model)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>conversation_id</code></td>
                        <td>integer</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Existing conversation to continue</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>history</code></td>
                        <td>array</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Previous messages for context (optional, for stateless API clients)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <h3>Conversations Endpoint</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>GET /ai/conversations</code></p>
                <p>
                    Retrieve user's conversation history.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Response:</strong> Array of conversation objects with metadata and message counts</p>
            </section>
            
            <section id="form-endpoints">
                <h2>Web Form Endpoints</h2>
                
                <h3>Query Form</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>GET /ai/query_form</code></p>
                <p>
                    Displays HTML form for single-shot AI queries. Requires authentication.
                </p>
                
                <h3>Result Handler</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>POST /ai/result</code></p>
                <p>
                    Processes form submissions and displays AI response in template.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Parameters: prompt (required), format (optional), system (optional)
                </p>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>ℹ Form Endpoints:</strong> Require authenticated user. Guests should use JSON API endpoints instead.
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="conversations">
                <h2>Conversation Management</h2>
                
                <h3>Multi-Turn Conversations</h3>
                <p>
                    The AI controller supports persistent, multi-turn conversations with history:
                </p>
                
                <h3>Conversation Workflow</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>User sends first message → New <code>AiConversation</code> created</li>
                    <li>System creates <code>AiMessage</code> record for user message</li>
                    <li>AI responds and creates <code>AiMessage</code> record for AI response</li>
                    <li>User sends follow-up with <code>conversation_id</code> → Message added to existing conversation</li>
                    <li>Conversation history retrieved automatically for context</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>Conversation Methods</h3>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Method</th>
                        <th>Route</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>conversations</code></td>
                        <td>GET /ai/conversations</td>
                        <td>List all conversations for user</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>reset_conversation</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/reset_conversation</td>
                        <td>Clear conversation history (hard reset)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <h3>Database Tables</h3>
                <p>
                    Conversation data persisted in:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>ai_conversations</code> - One row per conversation (id, user_id, created_at, updated_at)</li>
                    <li><code>ai_messages</code> - One row per message (id, conversation_id, user_id, role, content, created_at)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <strong>⚠ Database Issue (Tracked):</strong> Conversation records not persisting despite code presence.
                    See <a href="#database-blocker">Database Blocker</a> section below.
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="model-management">
                <h2>Model Management</h2>
                
                <h3>Model Browser</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>GET /ai/models</code></p>
                <p>
                    Display available and installed Ollama models across configured servers.
                </p>
                
                <h3>Model Operations</h3>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Method</th>
                        <th>Route</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>pull_model</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/pull_model</td>
                        <td>Download and install model from registry</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>test_model</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/test_model</td>
                        <td>Test loaded model with sample prompt</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>remove_model</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/remove_model</td>
                        <td>Unload and delete model from server</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <h3>Model Status</h3>
                <p><strong>Route:</strong> <code>GET /ai/check_status</code></p>
                <p>
                    Real-time status of Ollama server and loaded models.
                </p>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>ℹ Admin-Only:</strong> Model management requires admin, developer, or editor role.
                    Regular users can only query models.
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="server-management">
                <h2>Server Management</h2>
                
                <h3>Server Configuration</h3>
                <p>
                    AI controller supports multiple Ollama servers:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>localhost:11434</strong> - Local development/testing</li>
                    <li><strong>192.168.1.199:11434</strong> - Network AI server (production)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Server Configuration Methods</h3>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Method</th>
                        <th>Route</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>set_host</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/set_host</td>
                        <td>Configure active Ollama server (admin-only)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>start_server</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/start_server</td>
                        <td>Start Ollama service on local machine</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>server_status</code></td>
                        <td>GET /ai/server_status</td>
                        <td>Get connection status and diagnostics</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <h3>Permission-Based UI</h3>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>User Role</th>
                        <th>Can Select Server</th>
                        <th>Can See Details</th>
                        <th>Server Options</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Admin/Developer/Editor</td>
                        <td>✅ Yes</td>
                        <td>✅ Yes (host:port)</td>
                        <td>Local + Network</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Regular User</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>❌ No (hidden)</td>
                        <td>Network only (unlabeled)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </section>
            
            <section id="implementation-details">
                <h2>Implementation Details</h2>
                
                <h3>JSON Body Parsing</h3>
                <p>
                    Robust JSON body parsing with fallback to form parameters:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Check Content-Type for application/json</li>
                    <li>Try $c->req->content() method (preferred)</li>
                    <li>Fallback to $c->req->body() if needed</li>
                    <li>Log body length and first 200 chars for debugging</li>
                    <li>Parse JSON with error handling</li>
                    <li>Fall back to form parameters if JSON parsing fails</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>Logging</h3>
                <p>
                    Comprehensive debug logging enabled:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Method entry/exit logging</li>
                    <li>Parameter validation logging</li>
                    <li>User/guest session tracking</li>
                    <li>Ollama connection attempts and results</li>
                    <li>Conversation creation/retrieval logging</li>
                    <li>Error logging with stack traces</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <strong>Enable Debug Mode:</strong> Add <code>?debug=1</code> to URL or check <code>$c->session->{debug_mode}</code>
                </p>
                
                <h3 id="database-blocker">Database Recording Blocker (Known Issue)</h3>
                <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6b6b; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                    <strong>🔴 CRITICAL:</strong> Conversation and message database records not persisting despite code execution.
                    
                    <p><strong>Symptoms:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Code executes without errors in logs</li>
                        <li>AiConversation/AiMessage create() calls complete</li>
                        <li>No records appear in database tables</li>
                        <li>Next queries fail to find conversation</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p><strong>Probable Causes (Priority):</strong></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Table name mismatch: Result classes declare <code>ai_conversations</code>/<code>ai_messages</code>, actual tables may differ</li>
                        <li>Schema not deployed: Tables don't exist in database</li>
                        <li>Foreign key constraint: Guest user (id=199) missing from users table</li>
                        <li>Silent exception in database layer</li>
                    </ol>
                    
                    <p><strong>Verification Queries:</strong></p>
                    <pre><code>SHOW TABLES LIKE '%ai%';
DESCRIBE ai_conversations;
DESCRIBE ai_messages;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ai_conversations;
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 199;
                    </code></pre>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="methods-reference">
                <h2>Complete Methods Reference</h2>
                
                <h3>Main Actions (Routed Endpoints)</h3>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <tr>
                        <th>Method</th>
                        <th>Route</th>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>Auth</th>
                        <th>Purpose</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>index</code></td>
                        <td>GET /ai</td>
                        <td>Page</td>
                        <td>None</td>
                        <td>Main AI interface with query form</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>generate</code></td>
                        <td>POST /ai/generate</td>
                        <td>API JSON</td>
                        <td>None</td>
